Q9. Create visualizations using ggplot2.
Answer
R
Copy code
install.packages("ggplot2")
library(ggplot2)

# Histogram
ggplot(data, aes(x = Salary)) +
  geom_histogram(fill = "blue") +
  labs(title="Salary Distribution", x="Salary", y="Frequency")

# Box plot
ggplot(data, aes(x = Gender, y = Salary)) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(title="Salary by Gender")

# Scatter plot
ggplot(data, aes(x = Age, y = Salary)) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(title="Age vs Salary")
Explanation:
Histogram distribution show karta hai, boxplot variation aur scatter plot relationship show karta hai.

Q10. Perform linear regression and logistic regression.
Answer
R
Copy code
# Linear regression
model1 <- lm(Salary ~ Age + Experience, data = data)

summary(model1)

# Logistic regression
model2 <- glm(Purchased ~ Age + Salary,
              data = data,
              family = binomial)

summary(model2)

# Export results to CSV
write.csv(summary(model1)$coefficients, "linear_results.csv")
Interpretation:
Regression coefficients batate hain ki independent variables dependent variable ko kitna affect karte hain.





